&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Juris Doctor degree from an accredited law school.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active license to practice law and in good standing in at least one U.S. jurisdiction; North Carolina licensure or eligibility for North Carolina in-house counsel registration preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–4 years of relevant legal experience, preferably with exposure to corporate transactions, commercial contracts, contract negotiation, and general corporate matters.&lt;/li&gt;
